reviews.title: Great Sound and Comfort .
reviews.review_text: These headphones deliver very good sound quality with strong bass and clear calls. The noise cancellation works well, especially for this price range. They are comfortable to wear for long periods, and the battery life is impressive — lasting as advertised. Recommend it!

reviews.title: Very Good value for the Price.
reviews.review_text: I recently picked up these Wireless Bluetooth Headphones and have been really impressed with their performance. The 5.4 Bluetooth connection is super stable, and the 40-hour battery life is an exaggeration,— It is more like 28 hours without needing to recharge. The three EQ modes are a nice touch, letting me switch between settings for music, calls, or just drowning out background noise. The four-mic ENC noise cancellation works well for calls; people on the other end say I sound clear even when I'm in a noisy environment. The bass boost is noticeable and adds a nice punch to music without sounding muddy. Comfort-wise, they fit nicely over the ears and don't cause fatigue even during long sessions. My only mild critique — and the reason I'm holding back that fifth star — is that the ear cups could be a bit more plush for extended wear. But overall, these are a solid choice for travel, home, or office use. Great value for the price!

reviews.title: Very nice headphones

reviews.title: Fake Discount, Real Disappointment
reviews.review_text: I thought I scored a deal getting these IKT headphones for $21, supposedly marked down from $126. Turns out the price is always $21 — the $126 is just a fake crossed-out number to make it look like a bargain. On top of that, the quality is awful. The plastic feels cheap, the sound is tinny, and the noise cancellation? Completely useless. I can still hear my lawn mower and even my neighbor's while cutting grass. Don't fall for the fake discount — these aren't even worth the $21.
